# Integrate Spring Security with Production-Ready JWT Authentication

This plan integrates Spring Security 7 with JWT-based stateless authentication into the existing E-Commerce Order Management System (Spring Boot 4.0.4). It covers the full auth lifecycle: registration, login, token refresh, role-based access control, and secure error handling.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Role Enum Mismatch**: The database migration `V3` defines `user_role` as `('ADMIN', 'USER')`, but the Java enum `Role.java` uses `CUSTOMER` instead of `USER`. The seed data `V2` also inserts `'CUSTOMER'`. This will cause issues. I recommend adding a Flyway migration to add `'CUSTOMER'` to the PostgreSQL enum and keeping the Java enum as-is (`ADMIN`, `CUSTOMER`).

> [!WARNING]
> **Existing Plaintext Passwords**: The seed data stores passwords as plaintext (`'password'`). After this integration, all new users will have BCrypt-hashed passwords. The migration will re-hash the existing sample passwords so login works immediately.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **JWT Secret Key**: The plan stores the signing key in `application.yaml` for development. For production, this MUST be loaded from an environment variable or a secrets vault (e.g., `${JWT_SECRET}`). The plan sets this up with a default-with-env-override pattern.

