### 3. Security Infrastructure (`security` package)

#### [NEW] `security/SecurityConfig.java`
The main `@Configuration` class defining:
- `SecurityFilterChain` bean ‚Äî disables CSRF, sets stateless session, defines public vs protected endpoints
- `PasswordEncoder` bean (BCrypt)
- `AuthenticationManager` bean
- JWT filter registration (before `UsernamePasswordAuthenticationFilter`)
- Custom `AuthenticationEntryPoint` for 401 responses
- Custom `AccessDeniedHandler` for 403 responses

**Authorization rules:**
| Path Pattern | Access |
|---|---|
| `POST /api/auth/**` | Public (permit all) |
| `POST /api/products/**` | `ADMIN` only |
| `PUT /api/products/**` | `ADMIN` only |
| `DELETE /api/products/**` | `ADMIN` only |
| `GET /api/products/**` | Authenticated |
| `GET /api/orders/user/{userId}` | Authenticated (service layer enforces ownership) |
| `POST /api/orders` | Authenticated |
| `GET /api/users/**` | Authenticated |
| Everything else | Authenticated |

#### [NEW] `security/JwtAuthenticationFilter.java`
`OncePerRequestFilter` that:
1. Extracts `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header
2. Parses and validates the JWT via `JwtService`
3. Loads `UserDetails` and sets `SecurityContextHolder` authentication
4. Passes through to the next filter on any error (letting the `AuthenticationEntryPoint` handle it)

#### [NEW] `security/JwtAuthenticationEntryPoint.java`
Returns a structured `ApiResponse` JSON body with HTTP 401 for unauthenticated requests.

#### [NEW] `security/CustomAccessDeniedHandler.java`
Returns a structured `ApiResponse` JSON body with HTTP 403 for unauthorized requests.

#### [NEW] `security/UserDetailsImpl.java`
Implements `UserDetails`, wrapping the `User` entity. Maps `Role.ADMIN` ‚Üí `ROLE_ADMIN`, `Role.CUSTOMER` ‚Üí `ROLE_CUSTOMER`.

#### [NEW] `security/UserDetailsServiceImpl.java`
Implements `UserDetailsService`, loading user by username from `UserRepository`.

