### 9. Database Migration

#### [NEW] `src/main/resources/db/migration/V4__create_refresh_tokens_table.sql`

```sql
CREATE TABLE refresh_tokens (
    id            UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    token         VARCHAR(512) NOT NULL UNIQUE,
    user_id       UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    expires_at    TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    revoked       BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT FALSE,
    created_at    TIMESTAMP NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW()
);

CREATE INDEX idx_refresh_tokens_token ON refresh_tokens(token);
CREATE INDEX idx_refresh_tokens_user_id ON refresh_tokens(user_id);
```

#### [NEW] `src/main/resources/db/migration/V5__hash_existing_passwords.sql`

> [!NOTE]
> This uses pgcrypto's `crypt()` / `gen_salt()` to BCrypt-hash existing plaintext passwords directly in PostgreSQL, so the app can authenticate seed data users immediately.

```sql
UPDATE users SET password = crypt(password, gen_salt('bf', 10));
```

