## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> 1. **Role Enum Fix**: Should I add a Flyway migration to add `'CUSTOMER'` to the existing `user_role` PostgreSQL enum (since it currently only has `'ADMIN'` and `'USER'`)? Or would you prefer to change the Java enum to use `USER` instead of `CUSTOMER`?

> [!IMPORTANT]
> 2. **Password Hashing in DB**: The `V5` migration uses `pgcrypto` to hash existing plaintext passwords directly. This BCrypt implementation is compatible with Spring Security's `BCryptPasswordEncoder`. Are you okay with this approach, or do you want to handle seed data differently?

> [!IMPORTANT]
> 3. **`@PreAuthorize` on Controllers**: Should I add method-level security annotations (`@PreAuthorize`) to controllers for fine-grained access (e.g., only ADMIN can create products, customers can only see their own orders), or do you prefer to handle authorization purely at the URL-pattern level in `SecurityConfig`?

